problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in philosophy would. What is the molecular formula of methyl (3S)-3-amino-4-methylhexanoate?
Answer:
gpt_response:
The molecular formula of methyl (3S)-3-amino-4-methylhexanoate can be determined by first identifying the structural formula of the compound. In this case, we have a 3-amino-4-methylhexanoate group attached to a methyl group at the 3S position. 

Breaking down the structural formula, we can identify the components: 
1. The base structure is a hexanoate group (C6H12O2)
2. Attached to the fourth carbon of the hexanoate group is a methyl group (CH3)
3. Attached to the third carbon of the hexanoate group is an amino group (NH2)

Putting these components together, we get the molecular formula of methyl (3S)-3-amino-4-methylhexanoate as C8H17NO2.
